overview: The user initiated a project to enhance their sleep questionnaire
  application by integrating a database and an admin dashboard. The core
  implementation involved setting up a PostgreSQL database via NeonDB and
  Prisma, creating a  model to store detailed
  questionnaire data, and developing API endpoints for saving and retrieving
  responses. An admin dashboard was built, featuring a login page, a table to
  display submitted responses, and a CSV export option. Initially, a custom
  session-based authentication system was developed, but it was subsequently
  simplified by leveraging Next.js middleware for more efficient route
  protection and a straightforward cookie-based session. The project also
  included updating the questionnaire form to capture and store the new
  demographic data and ensuring all components worked seamlessly. The database
  setup and functionality were thoroughly tested in the browser.
